        "solution": "Assume for contradiction that n is prime. By Wilson’s Theorem, (n−1)! ≡ −1 (mod n). However, the hypothesis states n | (n−1)!, which implies (n−1)! ≡ 0 (mod n). This leads to 0 ≡ −1 (mod n), which is impossible for n > 1. Therefore, n must be composite."
